-- Shanghai Curbs Overseas Travel by City Officials, Xinhua Reports
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2013-09-23T23:55:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-09-23/shanghai-curbs-overseas-travel-by-city-officials-xinhua-reports.html
Shanghai has ordered city
government and Communist Party officials to end unnecessary
travel overseas, the official Xinhua News Agency reported.  No training should be done overseas using government funds
if it can be completed at home, the news agency reports. The
size of groups traveling abroad and the length of trips should
also be strictly controlled, according to the report, citing a
circular issued on Sept. 22.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 John Liu  at 
 jliu42@bloomberg.net  